data.author: Woojin Wie
data.message:
chore: Update changelogs and .gitignore

- Added entries for handling lint errors across multiple packages.
- Updated .gitignore to include IDE cursor files.

data.author: Woojin Wie
data.message: doc: Add docstring to JointTrajectoryExecutor class for clarity

data.author: Woojin Wie
data.message:
refactor: Update initial positions and launch files for OpenManipulator

- Changed step name from `ready` to `home` in `initial_positions.yaml` for clarity.
- Updated launch files to replace `ExecuteProcess` with `Node` for `pack_unpack_y` and `joint_trajectory_executor`, improving consistency and readability.
- Removed unnecessary launch arguments in `hardware_y_follower.launch.py` to streamline configuration.
- Enhanced comments in launch files for better understanding of execution flow.

data.author: Woojin Wie
data.message:
refactor: Update launch files for Open Manipulator configuration

- Introduced a `robot_description` variable in `hardware_x.launch.py` for cleaner parameter handling.
- Renamed `robot_state_pub_node` to `robot_state_publisher_node` for clarity.
- Consolidated controller spawner nodes into a single `robot_controller_spawner` node.
- Removed commented-out code and unnecessary event handlers in `hardware_y_follower.launch.py` to improve readability.

data.author: Woojin Wie
data.message:
feat: Introduce joint trajectory executor and update launch configuration

- Added `joint_trajectory_executor.py` to handle joint trajectory execution.
- Removed `init_position_x.py` as its functionality is replaced by the new executor.
- Updated `setup.py` to register the new executor as a console script.
- Created initial position configuration files for Open Manipulator X, Y, and Y Follower.
- Modified `hardware_x.launch.py` to launch the joint trajectory executor instead of the previous init position script.
